#: ../../source/introduction.rst:786
msgid "Calling the Model Query and Manipulation API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:788
msgid ""
"In the OpenModelica System Documentation, an external API (application "
"programming interface) is described which returns information about "
"models and/or allows manipulation of models. Calls to these functions can"
" be done interactively as below, but more typically by program clients to"
" the OpenModelica Compiler (OMC) server. Current examples of such clients"
" are the OpenModelica MDT Eclipse plugin, OMNotebook, the OMEdit graphic "
"model editor, etc. This API is untyped for performance reasons, i.e., no "
"type checking and minimal error checking is done on the calls. The "
"results of a call is returned as a text string in Modelica syntax form, "
"which the client has to parse. An example parser in C++ is available in "
"the OMNotebook source code, whereas another example parser in Java is "
"available in the MDT Eclipse plugin."
msgstr ""

